<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text">Trees have thin bark and can be killed or scarred by cool fires. Most open subalpine stands have discontinuous surface fuel, which limits fire spread to a small area. Scars provide vectors for butt rots to enter trees (Sugihara et al. 2007).</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
